# Library Management System

A console-based Library Management System developed in C++ using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP). The application helps manage books, members, and borrowing operations through a simple menu-driven interface.

## Features

* Add new books
* Add new members
* Issue books
* Return books
* Search books by ID
* Search books by title
* Search books by author
* Display all books
* Duplicate Book ID validation
* Duplicate Member ID validation
* Empty field validation
* Custom exception handling

## Technologies Used

* C++
* Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
* STL Vector
* Exception Handling

## Project Structure

* **Book Class**: Stores book details such as ID, title, author, and issue status.
* **Member Class**: Stores member details such as ID and name.
* **Library Class**: Manages all library operations including adding, searching, issuing, and returning books.

## Exception Handling

The project uses custom exceptions to handle:

* Duplicate Book IDs
* Duplicate Member IDs
* Empty input fields

## How to Compile and Run

### Using g++

```bash
g++ Library_Management_System.cpp -o LMS
./LMS
```

### Using clang++

```bash
clang++ -std=c++17 Library_Management_System.cpp -o LMS
./LMS
```

